MyShell (mysh)


A custom POSIX-compliant shell implementation supporting both interactive and batch processing modes.
Features


Core Functionality

Interactive command-line interface
Batch mode for script execution
POSIX-compliant stream I/O operations
Built-in command support
Process creation and management
Environment variable handling


Advanced Features

Input/Output redirection (>, <, >>)
Pipeline support for command chaining (|)
Wildcard pattern matching (*, ?)
Conditional command execution (&&, ||)
Background process execution (&)


Getting Started
Prerequisites

GCC or compatible C compiler
POSIX-compliant operating system
Make build system
